# Semgrep path exclusions
#
# frontend/src: ~80 jsx-not-internationalized findings excluded — this is a demo application
# and i18n is explicitly out of scope. react-props-spreading in test setup is intentional RTL usage.
frontend/src/

# cdk-outputs-lambda.json: Cognito UserPoolClientId and CloudFront header value trigger generic-api-key
# false positives — same values suppressed in .checkov.yaml and .gitleaksignore
cdk/cdk-outputs-lambda.json

# tests/: unit + integration tests. Semgrep findings here (string-concat-in-list in
# fixtures, useless-inner-function in test doubles, hardcoded-tmp-path) are test-only
# and carry no production risk. Bandit excludes tests/ via pyproject.toml for the same reason.
tests/

# notebooks/: Jupyter eval/demo notebooks — not deployed runtime code. The flagged
# "token" lines are runtime-minted M2M tokens / variable assignments, not literals.
notebooks/

# cowork/: local developer MCP onboarding scripts + an EXAMPLE env file (config.env.example).
# unquoted-variable-expansion-in-command is in operator-run setup scripts (values are
# operator-provided, not untrusted); the example file ships placeholders, not secrets.
cowork/

# Dockerfiles: `dockerfile-source-not-pinned` fires on AWS-managed base images
# (public.ecr.aws/lambda/*) which AWS pins + patches; pinning to a digest would block
# those security updates. Accepted across all Lambda image Dockerfiles.
**/Dockerfile

# frontend/package.json: `package-dependencies-check` on pinned demo dependencies —
# dependency CVEs are tracked separately via Dependabot (see GitHub security tab).
frontend/package.json
